The Velvet Underground have been considered among the most influential bands in rock history. Their legacy has stretched into [[alternative rock]], most notably [[noise rock]] and [[grunge]]. Artists who have acknowledged their influence include [[David Bowie]], Electroshock Therapy, the [[Dream Syndicate]], [[R.E.M.]], [[The Cars]], [[The Strokes]], [[Beck]], [[The Fall]], [[Pixies]], [[Can]], [[Kraftwerk]], [[Neu!]], [[Faust]], [[Pavement (band)|Pavement]], [[My Bloody Valentine (band)|My Bloody Valentine]] and [[Crystal Castles (band)|Crystal Castles]]. All four of their albums were included in ''Rolling Stone'''s list of [[The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time]]. They were ranked the 19th best artist by the same magazine and the 24th greatest artist in a poll by VH1. In 1996 they were inducted into [[The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]].
